  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacitating GHARWEG</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Gharweg is a long established charity primarily focused on providing training and advice to help people in the UK access employment, funded by a range of institutional and charitable donors. They also support two projects in northern Ghana funded by DFID and Comic Relief. Gharweg have prudently managed their growth and activities over many years and recently recovered from a funding crisis. But they remain dependant on restricted donations and service contracts, and the bulk of their funding is renewed on an annual basis so they can never be certain about future income. Their board appreciate that difficult times lie ahead for small charities; they face a tougher and more competitive funding environment. They want to develop a stronger funding base and expand their work in Africa. This grant will provide technical support to help them develop effective business and fundraising plans.</narrative>
  </description>
